{{primitive|x/y}}

'''Base encode''' or just '''encode''' takes a digit array <code>y</code> and encodes it into a single number using the bases in <code>x</code>.

If <code>x</code> is an atom, repeats it for all elements in <code>y</code>.

<pre>
 2 2 2/1 0 1
5
 2/1 0 1
5
 10 10 10/3 4 5
345
</pre>

